        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the mixture",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional. Line a baking tray with baking paper. Melt the butter, golden syrup, and sugar together in a saucepan over low heat until the sugar dissolves. Remove from the heat. Sift in the flour and ginger and stir until smooth. Add the lemon juice. The mixture will be thin and loose.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake in small batches",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drop 4 teaspoons of mixture onto the tray, well apart (at least 8 cm between each). Bake for 7 to 8 minutes until each disc is golden brown throughout and the surface has a bubbled, lacy appearance. Remove from the oven. Working quickly, lift one disc at a time and roll it tightly around the handle of a wooden spoon. Hold for 5 seconds, then slide off and rest seam-side down on the rack. If a disc sets before you reach it, return it to the oven for 30 seconds. Repeat with the remaining mixture.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and serve",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whip the cream with the icing sugar and vanilla to firm peaks. Transfer to a piping bag. Pipe cream into both ends of each snap cylinder just before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
